  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of anxiety?",
  "response": "Anxiety can manifest through a wide range of symptoms, which can be **physical**, **emotional**, **cognitive**, and **behavioral**. Symptoms vary from person to person, but common signs include:\n\n---\n\n### **Physical Symptoms**\n- Rapid heartbeat or palpitations\n- Shortness of breath or feeling like you can\u2019t catch your breath\n- Sweating or chills\n- Trembling or shaking\n- Muscle tension or aches\n- Fatigue or feeling drained\n- Upset stomach, nausea, or diarrhea\n- Headaches or dizziness\n- Chest tightness or pain (can mimic heart attack symptoms)\n- Dry mouth or difficulty swallowing\n\n---\n\n### **Emotional Symptoms**\n- Feeling nervous, restless, or on edge\n- Overwhelming fear or dread\n- Irritability or mood swings\n- Feeling like something bad is going to happen (sense of impending doom)\n- Difficulty focusing on anything other than the worry\n\n---\n\n### **Cognitive Symptoms**\n- Racing thoughts or uncontrollable overthinking\n- Difficulty concentrating or memory problems\n- Catastrophizing (assuming the worst will happen)\n- Inability to relax or quiet the mind\n- Excessive worry about everyday situations\n\n---\n\n### **Behavioral Symptoms**\n- Avoiding situations or places that trigger anxiety\n- Procrastination or difficulty making decisions\n- Restlessness (e.g., fidgeting, pacing)\n- Difficulty sleeping or staying asleep (insomnia)\n- Nail-biting, skin-picking, or other repetitive behaviors\n- Social withdrawal or isolation\n\n---\n\n### **Panic Attacks**\nIn some cases, anxiety can escalate into a **panic attack**, which includes intense symptoms such as:\n- Overwhelming fear or terror\n- Rapid heartbeat or chest pain\n- Difficulty breathing or hyperventilation\n- Feeling like you\u2019re losing control or \u201cgoing crazy\u201d\n- Numbness or tingling in the hands or feet\n- Fear of dying\n\n---\n\nIf anxiety symptoms are persistent, severe, or interfere with daily life, it\u2019s important to seek help from a mental health professional. Treatment options, such as therapy, medication, or lifestyle changes, can be highly effective in managing anxiety.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
